<paragraph blockId="7.[138,1185,284,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="2377">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1910" box="[282,477,415,439]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Periacma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="2377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iodesma">
<emphasis box="[282,477,415,439]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2377">Periacma iodesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1894" box="[696,926,415,439]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Periacma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="2377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orthiodes">
<emphasis box="[696,823,415,439]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="2377">P. orthiodes</emphasis>
Meyrick
</taxonomicName>
both superficially and in genitalia. It can be differentiated from the latter by the uncus with the caudal margin nearly straight, the gnathos with the anterior margin bluntly rounded, and the aedeagus with more than two tooth-like spines in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
